originalText.text:
The Primal Dance workshop was unlike anything I’ve done before. Jonathan is super knowledgeable and made learning how to crawl and roll on the ground fun and satisfying. My posture improved immediately.

He made me feel comfortable and safe while exploring new ways of moving and working with energy, and showed me how to adapt the movements to my specific needs.

The touch based healing felt truly amazing, like an exchange of pure, clean energy that was deeply rejuvenating and he encouraged me to share and honor my personal boundaries; it’s hard to put into words but it was quite the experience.

originalText.text: What an amazing event that Jonathan hosted for my 11 year old daughter’s birthday! American Ninja Obstacle course that balance strength building, team collaboration and balance. I highly recommend this type of event for future kids parties - all of the kids loved competing and cheered each other on throughout. They especially enjoyed being with someone who has competed on America Ninja Warrior.

originalText.text: Jonathan has shown me a method of deep self-exploration through movement that has benefited me immensely. I'm enjoying learning about myself and my body, and how freaking powerful that it is. Through Jonathan’s guidance and energy I have been able to begin a process of healing internally and externally. My anxiety has generally improved, thus allowing me to be more ‘present.’ In my everyday dance/movement classes and in audition scenarios, I am able to perform better by making more efficient choices. Similarly, I show up to the studio in a more connected and empowered way. Jonathan has changed my life  all for the better.

originalText.text:
Mothers need love and care too but unfortunately are often the last in line. It's so clear that Jonathan loves and values mothers, what a relief! His presence always has a calming, comforting effect on me, not exactly a common quality for personal trainers.

I'm someone who loves working hard (I'm a 2x Golden Gloves silver medalist) but rather than push me into over training, Jonathan was very holistic and systematic in his approach.

First, he really helped me heal from the trauma of pregnancy/IVF and set up the foundation for me to be healthier and stronger than ever. We focused on primal movement, energy medicine (Qigong), and healing touch to help me reconnect to my body and increase my energy.

I enjoy being touched but after multiple rounds of IVF and  giving birth to twins I was definitely exhausted and under nourished sensually. The healing touch Jonathan does is just the right kind; it helped me relax deeply for the first time since becoming a mother, better appreciate my body and feel more comfortable in it, breathe better, and even improved my intuition.

Jonathan's approach is high touch and intimate. He always gets consent first and meets me where I'm at each day, even though where I'm at shifts dramatically throughout my menstrual cycle.

Many of the techniques Jonathan taught me not only helped me personally but are tools that I use with my own children. For instance, the acupressure points for decreasing nausea helped me feel much better, and I also use them with my children when they need it.

He has such a playful spirit and this helped wake up my own inner child and made me a more joyful, playful mother.

This pleasure based  approach gave me the abundance of energy I need to start working hard again and get back into fighting shape.”

originalText.text: I felt truly GREAT after just one Primal Energy session. For the entire rest of the day I was  energized and happy. I had a great nite's sleep (which has been rare for me recently). I like that the practice is so simple and so easy.  If I can do it, anyone can! My shoulder is definitely feeling better. I don't have the excruciating pain that was becoming commonplace every day! Just by doing these small movements 5 - 10 minutes per day, I've become more focused and comfortable in my body.
